			<div class="content" id="post-content-1341709">
									

<p>Cons: I feel that I read about this idea in the d20 Cthulhu book. I am not sure that a 2 meter electric fence is much of a deterrent, nor is 10 guards in junkyard uniforms. Why are they feeding it D class personnel? how does one electromagnetic crane patrol 1.5&#160;km of perimeter? A breach on two fronts would be uncontainable in any case. Flyovers to measure the perimeter? They didn't encounter the red sky? There are other problems as well, but I don't want to grind it down too much.</p>
<p>Pros: &#8230;&quot;Extended incursions into SCP-967 have revealed the presence of detritus and derelict vehicles inconsistent with the current level of human technology.&quot; This is perhaps the diamond in the rough. Make it a normal junkyard with clutter appearing from different eras, with failing combat cyborgs patching themselves with scrap. The picture is a keeper as well.</p>
<p>I agree with the previous posters, it is very similar to others. Dr Gravity summed it best; &quot;Not bad as first tries go,<br />
I'd suggest taking it down then re-editing it into something more interesting.</p>
<p>And please, please, please use the chat to edit, that's what it's there for.&quot;</p>

